LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE SENATE
SENATE BILL NO. 1033
BY AGRICULTURAL AFFAIRS COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO AGRICULTURAL NUISANCE ACTIONS; AMENDING SECTION 22-4505, IDAHO
3 CODE, TO PROVIDE FOR ATTORNEY'S FEES AND PENALTIES FOR MERITLESS COM-
4 PLAINTS; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.
5 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
6 SECTION 1. That Section 22-4505, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
7 amended to read as follows:
8 22-4505. NUISANCE ACTIONS. (1) An agricultural operation, agricul-
9 tural facility or expansion thereof shall not be found to be a nuisance under
10 the circumstances described in section 22-4503, Idaho Code.
11 (2) An agricultural operation, agricultural facility or expansion
12 thereof that is operated in accordance with generally recognized agricul-
13 tural practices or in compliance with a state or federally issued permit
14 shall not be found to be a public or private nuisance. The provisions of
15 this subsection shall not apply when a nuisance results from the improper or
16 negligent operation of an agricultural operation, agricultural facility or
17 expansion thereof.
18 (3) If a public or private nuisance claim or cause of action is filed
19 against the owner or operator of an agricultural operation or the owner of
20 the land on which the agricultural operation is conducted and the applica-
21 ble court finds that the owner or operator is the prevailing party in the
22 action because the agricultural operation was conducted in accordance with
23 this chapter, then the owner or operator shall be entitled to receive its
24 reasonable attorney's fees and costs from the non-prevailing party.
25 (4)(a) Any person who files or makes more than one (1) meritless com-
26 plaint with the Idaho department of agriculture, the Idaho department
27 of environmental quality, the Idaho department of lands, or any other
28 state or local law enforcement agency against a specific agricultural
29 operation within a two (2) year period from the date of the first com-
30 plaint shall be subject to the following penalties:
31 (i) Filing or making a second meritless complaint within two (2)
32 years shall be an infraction and subject to a one hundred fifty
33 dollar ($150) fine.
34 (ii) Filing or making a third meritless complaint within two (2)
35 years shall be an infraction and subject to a three hundred dollar
36 ($300) fine.
37 (iii) Filing or making a fourth or subsequent meritless complaint
38 within two (2) years shall be a misdemeanor.
39 (b) For the purposes of this subsection, "meritless complaint" means
40 a complaint made or filed with the Idaho department of agriculture,
41 the Idaho department of environmental quality, the Idaho department of
42 lands, or any other state or local law enforcement agency alleging that

2
1 an agricultural operation constitutes a public or private nuisance as
2 described in this chapter when that agricultural operation was operat-
3 ing in compliance with this chapter at the time of the complaint.
4 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
5 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
6 July 1, 2025.

